5: Where you headed off to, Alice?
13:
*sigh* You'd better not be "running 
away" from home again.
17:
What? No! I'm just going for a walk, 
okay?!
22:
Are you okay on your own? I can 
come along, if you'd like!
25: Geez, stop treating me like a child!
29:
Hmph! They all need lessons on how 
to treat a lady the proper way!
38:
What're you doing here all by yourself
in a place like this? Don't you have a 
home to return to?
44:
Are you lost, little kitty?
I know how that feels.
46:
Are you hungry? Here... Do you want 
this biscuit? Do cats even eat biscuits?
52:
Looks like this one does, at least. You 
sure were lucky to run into me today, 
weren't you?
57:
You can't always rely on others to 
save you, even if you ARE cute.
59:
...Because life isn't all rainbows and 
sunshine, you know?
65: You don't have to follow me.
67: I can't take you home with me, okay?
73: I said I can't take you—
80:
Oh, come on! You're not allowed to 
look at me with those... adorable, 
widdle... eyes—I mean, no means NO!
86:
*sigh* I hope the little guy's okay. 
Perhaps I should've stuck around a 
little longer…
89:
No. That cat needs to learn to be 
strong! I did the right thing…
102: Huh? H-how did you find me here?!
115: A cat. What's it doing here?
118:
H-hey, don't look at me! It's not my 
fault he decided to follow me here!
131: What are you trying to do here?
134: I was hoping... I could touch it.
138:
You can't just approach a cat willy-
nilly! Here, nice and gentle... See?
146:
Wait, stop! Stop! Getting attached 
now is just gonna make leaving it 
harder!
156: Obviously! We can't keep it, right?
165: Huh? I mean... I guess no one.
167: B-but we already have a pet—Light!
176:
And we already have a cat... person, 
right? Nimbus! Maybe he won't get 
along with another cat, right?
183:
I mean, not only Nimbus! Isn't there a 
quota for how many furry-types are 
allowed in Starview or something?
193:
Um, er... I mean—
Ngh... Don't you get it, Stella?!
195:
What I'm trying to say is... I don't know
if I'm ready to take care of a cat on my 
own!
197:
I... don't know the first thing about 
being a mommy.
203:
Nonetheless, the cat has taken a liking
to you.
206: What do you want to do, Alice?
212:
I mean, will everyone else be okay 
with it?
225:
From today, this cat's staying here 
with me!
234:
Do you have a problem with that?
Because too bad! I won't have any of 
it!
240:
Alice... I'm so proud of you. *sniff*
You're really growing up!
248: Light... Are you seriously tearing up?
252:
Raising a pet is a big responsibility, 
Alice. Are you sure you can handle it?
256:
Of course! Who do you think I am? 
And besides, this guy's not that 
different from you, right?
264:
Furry-type... Are you referring to me?!
The Champion is no house cat! Or pet 
for that matter.
270:
Come here, little buddy... I think I'll call 
you Dinah.
